  override val startShort =
    "As the gentle warmth of late spring envelops the vibrant city of Rio de Janeiro, a sense of anticipation fills the air. It's in this setting—a harmonious blend of natural beauty and urban energy—that a luxurious getaway awaits within the plush comfort of a sleek vehicle." /
    "Guided by a driver whose features reflect the calming qualities of Rio itself, and whose knowledge is as deep as the culture that pulsates through these streets, we prepare to embark on a memorable journey through the city's iconic sites. As the sunlight caresses Rio's lively avenues and lush scenery, our hearts swell with the promise of discovering one of the world's most lively cities through eyes that have seen its many seasons." /
    "There, amidst the soft lapping of waves against the Copacabana shoreline and the rolling hills that proudly rise around us, lies the striking introduction to our day: Christ the Redeemer." /
    "We begin our tour nestled in the comfortable leather seats of our private vehicle, moving fluidly through Rio's bustling streets. The vivid urban life gently fades as we ascend the winding road towards Mount Corcovado." /
    "The path up is at once calming and exhilarating, offering occasional glimpses of the flecks of sunlight reflecting through the dense Tijuca rainforest. Our guide, with his mild assurance, entertains us with the story of Christ the Redeemer, how the idea was conceived, and the passion with which it was pursued, eventually leading to the placement of the cornerstone on a calm day in April nineteen twenty-two." /
    "Stepping out of the vehicle, we feel a gentle breeze, the forest's own breath, carrying the songs of tropical birds, as the sights of Rio de Janeiro stretch below us. As we approach the platform around the statue, we are awed by the enormity of this New Seven Wonder of the World." /
    "Christ the Redeemer, with arms wide spanning twenty-eight meters, stands as a symbol of peace over the city. Our guide points out that the statue rises to thirty meters tall, perched upon an eight-meter pedestal, gazing out to the horizon." /
    "Created with reinforced concrete and soapstone, the impressiveness of this vast figure humbles us. Designed by Heitor da Silva Costa, crafted by the artist Paul Landowski, and brought into being by Brazilian engineer Heitor Levy, this iconic edifice reflects a collaboration that transcends borders." /
    "We stand there, on the viewing platform, next to fellow observers who, like us, are eager to capture this panoramic beauty. Cameras click softly, preserving this moment where calmness envelops us, where the city and sky come together in a still alliance." /
    "Our fellow travelers graciously offer to take our picture with the statue framed by the sun's radiance—a memory immortalized in time. The feeling of unity amongst everyone here is evident as we all share in the appreciation of the city, the forest, and the ocean stretching out in a quiet acknowledgment to this dignified figure." /
    "This sense of peaceful quietude remains with us as we ready ourselves for the next part of our journey through Rio's enchanting streets."

  override val middleShort = listOf(
    "Our next destination is the Jardim Botânico, a lush oasis that stands as a verdant counterpoint to the bustling streets of Rio. Our limousine rolls to a stop at the entrance of these storied gardens, founded over two hundred years ago by King John the Sixth of Portugal." /
    "The scent of fresh earth and subtle blooms wafts through the open windows, inviting us to step out and immerse ourselves in this slice of paradise where spices like nutmeg, pepper, and cinnamon, once new and exotic to the Brazilian soil, were acclimatized from the West Indies." /
    "The garden unfolds over a staggering one hundred and forty hectares, and as our guide explains, it is a living library with around six thousand five hundred species, including those that teeter on the brink of extinction. We meander along the paths tiled with intricate designs, dwarfed by the famous Imperial Palm trees that stand as botanical sentinels, originally planted in the early nineteenth century." /
    "Their imposing presence is an echo of history rooted firmly in the earth." /
